♪Old stories like drifting dust♪

00:08:52.900 --> 00:08:57.780
♪Letters too short for my long feelings,
youth slips away♪

00:09:05.760 --> 00:09:07.560
Oh, my!

00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:08.480
That's a tough move!

00:09:09.040 --> 00:09:09.560
Oh…

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:11.520
Ugh…

00:09:12.440 --> 00:09:13.920
What's wrong with you?

00:09:14.360 --> 00:09:15.840
Why don't you lie down between them?

00:09:16.240 --> 00:09:16.840
Can I?

00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:17.200
OK.

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:17.680
Oi!

00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:20.600
Are you serious?

00:09:20.860 --> 00:09:23.120
You lie between them, they watch you,
and you watch them?

00:09:26.240 --> 00:09:28.960
Don't be silly, Yao.
I can just stand to the side and watch.

00:09:28.960 --> 00:09:30.200
With that brain of yours,

00:09:30.210 --> 00:09:32.890
it's a miracle you've survived this long
in the Chamber of Commerce.

00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:35.320
Musheng,

00:10:36.080 --> 00:10:37.600
I want to make a deal with you.

00:10:38.960 --> 00:10:40.640
If you help me,

00:10:42.440 --> 00:10:44.240
I'll be yours.

00:10:54.500 --> 00:10:55.840
So that's why you're seducing me.

00:10:56.920 --> 00:10:58.160
You want something.

00:10:59.920 --> 00:11:00.880
What's the matter?

00:11:02.880 --> 00:11:04.040
Don't want to, or don't dare?

00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:08.640
Go ahead.

00:11:09.120 --> 00:11:09.840
What do you want?

00:11:12.600 --> 00:11:13.800
Be my man.

00:11:17.720 --> 00:11:19.680
Who taught you to use your body

00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:21.280
as a bargaining chip?

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:23.480
You in or not?

00:11:24.320 --> 00:11:25.120
If not, get lost.

00:11:31.680 --> 00:11:32.480
Tell me why.

00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:34.080
Why do you want me

00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:37.040
to be your man?

00:11:41.720 --> 00:11:43.240
People like us,

00:11:43.720 --> 00:11:45.480
to survive in Night Shanghai,

00:11:46.040 --> 00:11:48.040
we need someone to back us.

00:11:50.080 --> 00:11:50.920
So

00:11:53.280 --> 00:11:55.520
I'm someone you can lean on, huh?

00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:57.280
Of course.

00:11:58.560 --> 00:12:01.640
You're the director of the Chamber
of Commerce's liaison office.

00:12:02.360 --> 00:12:03.720
I'd be a fool not to hold on tight.

00:12:07.600 --> 00:12:09.400
You better not regret it.

00:12:14.480 --> 00:12:15.720
Musheng,

00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:18.720
with that handsome face

00:12:20.060 --> 00:12:21.440
and that robust and muscular frame,

00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:25.240
no one fits the part better.

00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:26.920
(Let's see what it is)

00:12:27.360 --> 00:12:28.760
(you're really after.)

